overview: The user wanted to elevate the visual appeal of their sleep
  questionnaire app, which they felt was too generic. The agent began by
  thoroughly analyzing the existing design, identifying areas for improvement in
  color, typography, layout, and form elements. A new, calming sleep-themed
  color palette was introduced, and core UI components like checkboxes, radio
  buttons, sliders, and progress bars were redesigned for a more polished look.
  The main questionnaire form and intro section were revamped with subtle
  background elements, improved progress indicators, and feature cards.
  Crucially, the agent ensured consistent application of the new styling across
  all 14 questionnaire sections, transforming generic gray boxes into cohesive,
  themed cards. Additionally, a console error related to null values in input
  fields was identified and fixed, enhancing the app's stability. The overall
  outcome is a professional, visually appealing, and consistent user experience
  tailored for a sleep health application.
